name: DiagnosticReportProfile
title: DiagnosticReport Profile for Results Reporting
publisher: HL7 Canada - FHIR Implementation Work Group
description: Proposed constraints on the DiagnosticReport resource for the minimal set of data to query and retrieve diagnostic reports associated with laboratory and other results

element.definition: Diagnostic Report Profile is based upon the core FHIR DiagnosticReport resource and created to meet the Laboratory test(s) and Laboratory value(s)/result(s) requirements.
A code that classifies the Laboratory test(s) and Laboratory result(s). This is used for searching, sorting and display purposes.
element.comment: Multiple categories are allowed using various categorization schemes but at least one SHALL come from the FHIR defined value set that includes codes from HL7v2 Table 0074

element.definition: A code that classifies the Laboratory test(s) and Laboratory result(s). This is used for searching, sorting and display purposes.
element.comment: The code SHALL be LOINC 11502-2 'Laboratory report' code

element.definition: A code that classifies the report(s) or result(s). This is used for searching, sorting and display purposes.
element.comment: The code is preferrable comes from LOINC code system

element.short: Time of the report or note
element.definition: This is the Datetime or Period when the report or note was written.

element.comment: Details about the specimen(s) on which this laboratory report is based on.
Details about specimen(s) on which this report is based on.
Observations that represent results produced by laboratory tests or panels/studies
Observations that represent results produced for report

element.short: CHI identification of the condition, problem or diagnosis
element.definition: The code that represents relevant clinical problems, conditions, diagnoses, symptoms, findings and complaints taken from [CHI Health Concern Code](https://fhir.infoway-inforoute.ca/ValueSet/healthconcerncode)
element.comment: The binding strength of this element is [Example](https://www.hl7.org/fhir/terminologies.html#strength), meaning that the Canada Health Infoway Health Concern Code value set provides examples of the types of concepts intended to be included

binding.description: Represents the patient's relevant clinical problems, conditions, diagnoses, symptoms, findings and complaints, as interpreted by the provider.
